  <para>
    Cross sections are lines<footnote> <simpara>Maybe curves, in a
    later version of &oof2;.</simpara> </footnote> drawn on a &mesh;,
    at points along which <link
    linkend="Section-Output">Outputs</link> can be evaluated.  <xref
    linkend="RegisteredClass-CrossSectionDomain"/> is one of the <link
    linkend="RegisteredClass-Domain"><classname>Domains</classname></link>
    available to the commands in the <xref
    linkend="MenuItem-OOF.Mesh.Analyze"/> menu.
  </para>
  <para>
    In the GUI, the commands in the <command>CrossSection</command>
    menu are available in the <link
    linkend="Section-Graphics-CrossSection">Cross Section
    toolbox</link> and in the <guilabel>Domain</guilabel> pane of the
    <link linkend="Section-Tasks-Analysis">Analysis page</link>, when
    the domain is set to <userinput>Cross Section</userinput>.
  </para>



